Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Place @butter{4%tbsp}(plain) in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}; bring to room temperature.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces.

> Trim green beans if necessary or cut broccoli into bite-size pieces if necessary. Save potatoes for another use.

In a #large bowl{}, toss potatoes with a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle}, @Fry Seasoning{1%tbsp}, @salt{to taste}, and @pepper{to taste}; transfer to one side of a #baking sheet{}. Toss carrots on empty side of sheet with a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle}, salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, spread potatoes across entire sheet; toss carrots on a separate baking sheet.)

Roast on top rack until tender and browned, ~{20-25%minutes}. (For 4, roast potatoes on top rack and carrots on middle rack.)

> Swap in green beans for potatoes; toss as instructed. Roast carrots (without green beans) for 8 minutes. Remove sheet from oven and carefully add green beans to empty side. Roast 12-15 minutes more.

> Swap in broccoli for potatoes; toss as instructed. Roast carrots (without broccoli) for 5 minutes. Remove sheet from oven and carefully add broccoli to empty side. Roast 15-20 minutes more.

Peel and mince @garlic{2%cloves}(minced).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add garlic and @dried thyme{1%tsp}; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat; carefully transfer to bowl with @butter{5%tbsp}. Wipe out pan; let cool slightly.

Mash butter mixture with a #fork{}. (TIP: If butter is not yet softened, microwave for ~{10%seconds}.) Stir in @Worcestershire sauce{1%tbsp} and a pinch of pepper until combined.

Pat @Ranch steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in pan used for garlic over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

In the last minute of cooking, add 1 TBSP garlic herb butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings) to pan; let melt and spoon over steak until coated.

Transfer steak to a #cutting board{} to rest.

Once veggies are done roasting, melt @butter{1%tbsp}(plain) in a small #pot{} over medium-high heat.

Add @peas{4%ounce} and cook, stirring occasionally, until warmed through, ~{1%minute}. Remove from heat; stir in roasted carrots and @honey{2%tsp} until coated. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Thinly slice steak against the grain.

Divide steak, glazed peas and carrots, and potato wedges between plates. Top steak with as much remaining garlic herb butter as you like and serve.

> Store any leftover garlic herb butter in an airtight container in the fridge for up to 5 days.